==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Rennin
<hw>Ren"nin</hw> <pr>(r⟦ecr⟧n"n⟦icr⟧n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Biochem.)</fld> <def>A milk-clotting enzyme obtained from the true
stomach (abomasum) of a suckling calf. Mol. wt. about 31,000. Also
called <altname>chymosin</altname>, <altname>rennase</altname>, and
<altname>abomasal enzyme</altname>.</def> <au>[Merck Man. 11]</au>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Renning</ent>⟦br⟧
